<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Sinning unintentionally here is referring to a &quot;wandering&quot; sin where someone is still doing their best to follow God's commands but slips up. This is not referring to intentional defiant sin against God that is in the mind of you being above God's law.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Thankfully we have forgiveness in Christ for this kind of previous sin, but there was no forgiveness available through sacrifice for the Israelites.</li></ul></body></html>